title: Erectile Dysfunction Resources
author: WebMD Editorial Contributors

sections.heading: Organizations
content: If you think you may have ED, you'll want to learn as much as you can about the condition. There are plenty of resources to give you more information, including the following:
American Academy of Clinical Sexologists www.esextherapy.com
American Academy of Family Physicians (AAFP) www.aafp.org
American Association for Marriage and Family Therapy (AAMFT) www.aamft.org
American Association of Clinical Endocrinologists (AACE) www.aace.com
American Association of Sex Educators, Counselors, and Therapists (AASECT) www.aasect.org
American Diabetes Association (ADA) www.diabetes.org
American Urological Association www.auanet.org
National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases www.niddk.nih.gov
The Endocrine Society www.endo-society.org
